			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> Let's remember we dont Root, Snare, Cold, Poison, Lightning</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Does Maelstrom of Electricity count as lightening? <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
If you only look within your class, you won't do a very good job balancing its abilities against others. 
<br />

<br />
In controlled situations, pets provide a decent defense, however it is spotty at best, and certainly not good enough when compared to the balance that BL's achieve between DPS and defense. Most people have pointed out that their DPS is similar to that of a Mage, but they can tank, heal, and slow. 
<br />

<br />
I'm all for a solution that doesn't steal from other classes, but at this point, I don't see them making too many more enhancements to mage pets, without improving BL's and Necro's at the same time.
<br />

<br />
I guess my point is, our offensive DPS is nice, and situationally the best in the game (though many classes have situations where they can claim this), however, I don't feel that our offensive capability is so good that we should go without more defensive abilities (especially those that make soloing more viable).
<br />

<br />
The "best" way to fix this from a roleplay perspective would be to rewrite the aggro rules so that a pet could beat/taunt a mob off of the caster. Including the DDD pet, with a "functional" AE Taunt. This would be very helpful in cases where the mage would be stunned or rooted. However, long ago, Verant added a band-aid to the aggro system to say if any PC is in striking distance of a mob, the PC will be the target. This unfairly penalizes mages, because we can't take a hit, we can't root, we can't slow, we can't do anything but die.
<br />

<br />
Now, what are the solutions?
<br />

<br />
I mentioned one, but rewriting NPC aggro code would be very time intensive. Root/Slow/Snare would be another way to address this, especially if given to the mage in the form of a summoned, clickable item. This wouldn't require months of developer time to do either. 
<br />

<br />
I'd rather have a quick, practical fix now, than something that might or might not work 6 months from now.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Naladini Dreamfyre</a>
<br />
Arch Mage of 61 Seasons - <a href="http://stormhammer.dreamhost.com/forums" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stormhammer*</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
