And in fact it seems to me, based on what I've read of other high level mages, and the 3+ years of hearing "just wait until you get higher, you'll see how much pets suck" and personally discovering most of those assertions to either be flat out wrong or lacking in perspective, that the most frequent cause of pets becoming worthless for defense is the mage himself treating the pet like nothing more than a DoT.
<br />

<br />
Mobs that can 1-round a pet will probably be able to 2-round a rogue or a monk of a similar level.  By the time mob dps is that high, no one really survives unless proper support is given-- that means buffing and healing.   If you haven't even tried buffing and healing a pet, with a real healer such as a druid or cleric, then you are in no position to talk about a lack of pet defense.  And who knows, if you're lucky you'll trigger pet enrage, which is 10 whole seconds of frontal melee immunity.  That's pretty powerful no matter how hard the mob hits.
<br />

<br />
