				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Good points Solkain.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">OH another idea to add....solo missions...come on SoE you ripped off anarchy onlines Mission idea how about going a step further and actualy adding a storyline to your missions...also the timer is gay, sure it makes it so we gotta WORK through a mission. But whats the point of that, if I want xp I go to fire...UP the XP bonus. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Honestly, they could pull this off without having to make too many tweaks to characters. Just have a lot of NO RENT goodies waiting in each "mission" (CH Potions, DS Potions, etc).
<br />

<br />
As for solutions to the magician class, once again, it comes back to population. There aren't that many people playing mages relative to other classes, so asking for a lot of coding intensive fixes probably isn't going to happen. 
<br />

<br />
As I said in another thread, most AA problems in this game seem to center on class specific AA's (eg. FB, IRE, MB, Jamfest, etc.) The AA's that are shared across classes are the one's that generally work the best. Asking for unique magician abilities is good in principle, but bad in application. Even if SOE puts something creative together, there's little guarantee that it will work properly, and a decent probability that they won't go back and make it right.
<br />

<br />
Why? Too code intensive, and not enough people benefit from the change.
<br />

<br />
We need to stop asking for "all or nothing" solutions, and be willing to accept improvements, even if other classes have them already.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Naladini Dreamfyre</a>
<br />
