				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Anarchy online did it fairly well..What they did was made the mission area a fair distance away...the further you traveled to get to the mission the more the mission would be worth.
<br />

<br />
Soloing was made easier with "Medical kits" and "nano rechargers" basicly heal potions and Mana potions...Why not make these a viable optiona dn make them zone dependant? IE ONLY useable in the solo mission areas...BTW the items DID have reuse timers so you Couldn't sit in a battle healing yourself forever...
<br />

<br />
It would NOT be that hard to code in to the game...but realise that SoE never wants to spend money on deving this game too much...it a money market...but I ask...on a game that pulls more than 36 million a year WHY are they skimping on the dev and customer support / service?...thats another topic
<br />

<br />
Point is Solo missions are NOT that hard to implement, want a rough diagram SoE?? here...
<br />

<br />
Create a NPC in the camps called "Herbalist XXX" who sells solo mission packs which are only Buyable with GROUP mission points...this does several things for you all...it forces players to group and jump onto the time sink and money maker scheme as well as keeps players who like to play on Off hours...like in the Wee am hours interested in what LDoN has to offer.
<br />

<br />
Also make either another merchant for solo mission points. Or leave it how it is and make solo missions worth 1/2 as much points as a group encounter.
<br />

<br />
Seriously you all should have ripped off AO's idea a BIT better. their Idea for mission entrances EVERYWHERE was great in my honest opinion, but then again moving through AO was usualy a more dangerous task...COMPARE...a hard mission in AO would send you through a ToV like zone where beasts were everywhere that could kill you at will...avoiding them was part of the battle and the reward...
<br />

<br />
Maybe adding more mission entrances and making rewards based on several factors INSTEAD of JUST the monotonus go to XXX and do XXX for XXX...
<br />

<br />
okay back to magician upgrades...
<br />

<br />
Magicians are both Summoners and masters of the elements...which is why I have an orb of mastery = PP
<br />

<br />
WITH this in mind...an elemental slow / snare / mez / charm is not all that far fetched. DoTs aren't bad either, you can't tell me lava won't burn you over time if you stand in it or any of the other elements as well..
<br />

<br />
I do however think that Elemental dire charm will be near useless in the next expansion unless they add 3 to 6 zones where it would become a viable and useful AA. It certainly would be purely a BoT spell right now in the games current state...for those thinking about LDoN...no those elementals are too hight for DC, you will get DC proally around level 60 if we DO get it...and at that point all monsters in LDoN will be over 46.
<br />

<br />
Elemental slows is an idea a guildie mentioned to me. Personaly I don't know where this would be that viable to us, maybe as a reserve slower. But usualy whenever I go XPing in LDoN or doingmissions / whatnot we always have a Shm for Slows and heals or an Enc for slows and KEI's. I doubt this would change that much unless it slowed a elemental monster MORE than an enchanter / shm.
<br />

<br />
as said before...raise cap on Charm and mez...
<br />

<br />
Mass DS...another useful AA that should replace MGB Imho...
<br />

<br />
Either an elemental snare or an all out snare... the fact that random classes get this bothers me...druids...wizards...necromancers...clerics...
<br />

<br />

<br />
more to come later....
<br />

<br />
bored for now...</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
