			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The thing about saying magicians are about nukes, damage shields, and summoned stuff, is that other classes can do these things, or have means to substitute for these things.  Druids can ds, Beastlords have pets, Wizards can nuke, and you can loot or purchase focus items.  The things that make us truly unique from any other classes in the game are thus:
<br />

<br />
- We can potentially gain mana by reclaiming pets
<br />

<br />
- We can summon pet-only proccing weapons, a pet only Haste mask, and a belt that bestows stats and hit points.
<br />

<br />
- We can chain pets mana free, providing we have the AA's
<br />

<br />
- Our pets cast spells, rather than proc any innate abilities, and can land them on targets that may be impossible to land similar PC-based spells on.
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure where that puts us in terms of balance, or in terms of what we should be requesting or demanding, but this is my understanding of how our class works, and what makes us different.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
