				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have read so many places that a mage's defense is pet then Gate.
<br />

<br />
Well, that is shot in PoP. If the pet is gone after one round, I'm not getting Gate off with its over-four-second casting time. Healers aren't going to be able to react to that reliably either. 
<br />

<br />
Snare and/or slow would resolve that.
<br />

<br />
"Not correct from a role-playing perspective" -- BAH -- "You summon a net of goo over A_Nasty_Mob."
<br />

<br />
"Trivializes old content" -- So what's new? Vox/Naggy are level-limited now because of farmability issues. You can solo virtually our whole Kunark-era Epic, duoing the Crown. Soloing most of Kael Arena is trivial. It wouldn't surprise me if NToV were single-groupable. Emp/Seru are comfortable with somewhere in the 18-24 player range. Yes, one day the Rathe Council will be in the same range, but who will care? Time will be but for "stepping-stone" gear to whatever lies beyond. Farmability has been resolved by not having any significant number of valuable, tradable pieces on Velious and later bosses.
<br />

<br />

<br />
PoP effectively removed the "balance" mages had by relegating their pets to the scrap heap for DPS in many situations where it was once valuable. Valliant Companion and Protection of Calliv show that Verant, and to some extent SoE, wish to resolve it. Bring it back please. I wish to be a mage again, not a second-rate Wizzy. For that matter, Druids come close to my DPS when my pet is useless!
<br />

<br />
Summer's Flame -- Decrease Hitpoints by 1400 
<br />
Mana: 355 Skill: Evocation 
<br />
Casting Time: 6.25 Recast Time: 2.75 
<br />

<br />
Sun Vortex -- Decrease Hitpoints by 1550 
<br />
Mana: 395 Skill: Conjuration 
<br />
Casting Time: 6.35 Recast Time: 2.25
<br />

<br />
Druids have exactly the same Destroy Summoned as mages.
<br />

<br />
I get more requests for rings and bracers from Druids than any other class.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=568700" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
